5:
Ugh, isn't it a pain running around 
buying all the groceries? You get the 
exact same thing every week—just 
have it delivered!
8:
Would if I could, but the "W.F." is 
a secret. Still, I can't believe you made 
a color-coded grocery list. You sure 
are thorough.
12:
O-obviously! It's my JOB. What's with 
this list anyways? There's only 
a million different kinds of alcohol. 
Can't we just get one pack of beer and 
be done?
17:
I-I don't know! Apparently some of the 
older residents want to do a taste-
testing party to unwind a bit.
20:
Who cares? WE can't drink. If they want 
one of everything under the sun, they 
can go buy it their damn selves!
22:
Humph. I should've dragged someone 
along to carry the bags. Too late now, 
I guess. C'mon, hurry up or we'll be 
here all day.
26:
All right, Alk, listen. If you try to buy this 
much alcohol, it's not gonna be cheap, 
so we've gotta play it smart and 
haggle.
30:
I guess we could try, but I'm not very 
good at haggling.
34:
Well you're talking to a master. You be 
amazed how much a sweet teary 
maiden can knock off a price tag.
38:
A sweet maiden? I guess we could zip 
back to Starview and see if anyone 
wants to help us negotiate prices.
41:
Starview? When there's a sweet, 
adorable maid right here?
46:
Oh, I guess there IS the Maids' Parlor 
right nearby! Do you have someone 
specific in mind?
52:
...Y-you're doing that on purpose! Why 
do you think I bother with this 
eyepatch? Because it's CUTE, 
dumbass!
59:
Obviously! Why else would I lug 
around a toy and put up with TWO 
petticoats?! ...Just you watch!
62:
Why, hello there, sweetie. I'm afraid 
you aren't old enough to drink.
66:
*sniffle* I-I know, but... milord s-sent 
me to shopping for him and—hic—
I know this isn't enough, b-but...
71:
He—hic—he forgot to give me the 
money for it. I scraped together 
everything from my piggy-bank, but... 
*sniffle* This is all I—
81:
People are gonna think you mean ME! 
I'll never be able to show my face in 
Palpebra again!
89:
Ahaha! Oh, please. I could hear you 
two plotting the whole thing in the 
hallway. *wheeze* Man, I can't believe 
you thought that'd work.
92:
Whew, that was a good laugh. I'll give 
you a little discount for the show, but 
you're paying full price next time, 
okay?
97:
I'm glad he wasn't mad at us after 
your little skit. Now we're almost done 
shopping!
101:
Looks like the only thing left on the list 
is flour. There should be a miller over 
this way.
103:
Filthy street rat! Get away from my 
wares!
106:
Please, sir! Just enough to feed my 
brothers. I-I'll work to pay it off! 
Please...
107:
A dirty urchin like you? Non! You'd soil 
my wares. Now scram!
110: Hey! What do you think you're—
114:
Shhh. Don't shout. You'll make things 
worse.
121:
Heh, this is gonna be fun.
...Leave it to me—and play along this 
time.
126:
Oh, MY! Milord, I do believe that's the 
miller ALL the nobles were raving 
about! Why, I heard he supplies 
royalty!
131:
And look how charitable he is, giving 
bread to the poor! I heard the rumors, 
but I thought it was just talk.
135:
I've heard he refuses to accept a single 
coin from the needy—gives it all for 
free out of the goodness of his heart, 
bless him.
138:
Ahaha...ha... But of c-course! To s-
someone as wealthy as me, a few 
loaves are worth b-but pocket 
change! Free bread and grain for all! 
*whimper*
141:
I kinda feel bad now... Let's pay for ours 
properly.
144:
Bastard had it coming if you ask me. 
Hah! Look at him trying to flaunt how 
rich and magnanimous he is. I'm 
taking my free flour.
147:
He kinda did have it coming, honestly. 
It was funny, but I think you punished 
him plenty.
151:
Man, that ended up being an 
adventure, but now we're all set for the 
week.
155:
That was the most fun I've had running 
errands in a looong time.
157:
I'm looking forward to coming back 
next week.
